1
00:00:45,128 --> 00:00:47,297
Heeju, here's what we'll do.

2
00:00:47,965 --> 00:00:49,091
The gun?

3
00:00:52,219 --> 00:00:54,554
Actually, no.
You keep it just in case.

4
00:00:55,639 --> 00:00:56,640
Heeju.

5
00:00:57,432 --> 00:01:00,102
All you have to do is bring Detective Kim
to the mine. That's it.

6
00:01:01,228 --> 00:01:02,229
Got it?

7
00:01:02,896 --> 00:01:04,314
Yeah.

8
00:01:04,398 --> 00:01:05,691
If he tries anything funny...

9
00:01:06,942 --> 00:01:09,403
...just shoot him.
I'll take care of the rest.

10
00:01:37,347 --> 00:01:38,473
The gold bars?

11
00:01:39,725 --> 00:01:40,726
Get in.

12
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:42,644
I'm driving.

13
00:01:44,896 --> 00:01:46,565
You didn't bring a gun again,
did you?

14
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:49,943
No.

15
00:01:51,778 --> 00:01:53,196
Hey, what are you doing?

16
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,323
Stay still.

17
00:01:55,365 --> 00:01:57,117
Ah, geez.

18
00:02:22,059 --> 00:02:25,395
Hey, wh--what are you--
what are you doing?

19
00:02:25,896 --> 00:02:26,980
I'll release you from it later.

20
00:02:32,611 --> 00:02:34,529
Ah, shit.

21
00:02:44,456 --> 00:02:45,540
Where are we off to?

22
00:02:47,084 --> 00:02:48,377
An abandoned mine.

23
00:02:49,211 --> 00:02:50,212
In Jeongsan?

24
00:03:48,603 --> 00:03:54,276
EPISODE 9
CONSEQUENCES

25
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:04,661
GPS TRACKING

26
00:04:17,382 --> 00:04:21,386
DIRECTOR PARK
DETECTIVE KIM JINMAN

27
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:27,934
DIRECTOR PARK
DETECTIVE KIM JINMAN

28
00:04:41,198 --> 00:04:42,866
Do you still have 100 bars?

29
00:04:43,992 --> 00:04:45,285
Well, I guess not.

30
00:04:46,536 --> 00:04:51,333
You paid the hospital bills
and then you got those two cars.

31
00:04:52,918 --> 00:04:54,461
How many did you cash out?

32
00:04:57,714 --> 00:04:58,965
Only one.

33
00:04:59,049 --> 00:05:02,427
One? That's about 1.5 billion.

34
00:05:03,428 --> 00:05:04,679
That's not that bad.

35
00:05:06,431 --> 00:05:08,308
I'd say you can keep all that.

36
00:05:10,852 --> 00:05:13,104
You have your passport?
You ready to go?

37
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:15,607
Yes.

38
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:19,152
As soon as we've confirmed
the gold bars, get outta here.

39
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:21,613
Go as far away as you can.

40
00:05:26,451 --> 00:05:27,994
Don't worry about Sunok too much.

41
00:05:28,078 --> 00:05:29,329
I'll take good care of her.

42
00:05:32,707 --> 00:05:34,668
Why would you care for Aunt Sunok?

43
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:36,586
Did she not tell you?

44
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:39,130
We're old friends.

45
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:44,970
What kind of friend bugs his own friend?

46
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:47,639
I had to do it if I wanted to catch you.

47
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,684
I tried to tell you multiple times
I'd help you.

48
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:52,185
But you kept running away.

49
00:05:54,729 --> 00:05:57,440
Does anybody else in Geumseong know
that I have the gold bars?

50
00:05:57,524 --> 00:05:59,109
Other than you or Park?

51
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:02,946
Does Chairman Ahn know?

52
00:06:03,697 --> 00:06:05,073
He hasn't been told.

53
00:06:05,156 --> 00:06:06,992
Why haven't you told him yet?

54
00:06:07,075 --> 00:06:09,619
Didn't you say you were gonna give him
the gold bars anyway?

55
00:06:10,954 --> 00:06:12,747
Because I made a promise to your mother.

56
00:06:13,915 --> 00:06:15,000
I told her I'd save you.

57
00:06:17,794 --> 00:06:20,130
If I had told Chairman Ahn
about you,

58
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:21,673
you wouldn't be here.

59
00:06:22,632 --> 00:06:23,633
You'd be dead.

60
00:06:26,094 --> 00:06:29,264
You mean you never considered stealing all
the gold for yourself?

61
00:06:30,849 --> 00:06:33,268
You weren't planning on taking
the gold and just killing me

62
00:06:33,351 --> 00:06:35,395
like Park Hocheol killed Cha Yujin?

63
00:06:36,104 --> 00:06:38,273
Not at all.
Come on, seriously?

64
00:06:39,441 --> 00:06:40,692
That's what everyone says.

65
00:06:41,902 --> 00:06:43,737
In the beginning they all deny it,

66
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:45,780
but then they try to steal the gold bars
from me in the--

67
00:06:45,864 --> 00:06:48,033
CHAIRMAN AHN GYUSEOK

68
00:06:55,123 --> 00:06:56,416
Yes, hello, sir.

69
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:58,001
I've located the gold bars.

70
00:06:58,627 --> 00:07:00,128
At the abandoned mine in Jeongsan.

71
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:01,504
Yes.

72
00:07:02,756 --> 00:07:03,965
Yes, understood.

73
00:07:08,845 --> 00:07:10,388
You happy now? I did it.

74
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:16,686
Once you confirm the gold bars,
I'll let you go.

75
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:18,355
After that, Ahn and Park, they'll...

76
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:21,608
...they'll both leave you alone, okay?

77
00:07:26,905 --> 00:07:27,906
What?

78
00:07:28,907 --> 00:07:29,908
What now?

79
00:07:57,102 --> 00:07:58,436
How much further?

80
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,034
Over there.

81
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:17,706
Hey, take those off.

82
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,251
You need to guide us.
Come on.

83
00:08:43,356 --> 00:08:45,108
Hey, come on. What are you--

84
00:08:50,113 --> 00:08:51,114
What now?

85
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:53,950
Is this why you brought me all
the way out here?

86
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:55,994
Just so you could kill me?

87
00:09:00,665 --> 00:09:03,877
The gold bars aren't buried here,
are they? Right?

88
00:09:06,129 --> 00:09:07,380
If you aren't going to shoot me,
give it here.

89
00:09:07,464 --> 00:09:08,631
Don't come closer.

90
00:09:12,802 --> 00:09:14,763
Look, you heard me on the phone, right?

91
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:18,141
Chairman Ahn is on his way here right now!

92
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:20,101
You need to stop messing around!
This isn't a game!

93
00:09:20,185 --> 00:09:21,352
Tell me where the gold is!

94
00:09:21,436 --> 00:09:22,437
Whoa!

95
00:09:26,357 --> 00:09:27,358
It's really loaded.

96
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:29,778
What a crazy bitch.

97
00:09:29,861 --> 00:09:31,488
Were you really gonna kill him?

98
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:33,573
Hey, how did you find us here?

99
00:09:33,656 --> 00:09:36,493
I put a--a GPS tracker on her car.

100
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:38,787
Th--the app notified me that
the car was moving.

101
00:09:39,496 --> 00:09:40,705
I never thought you'd be
the one driving it.

102
00:09:40,789 --> 00:09:42,832
Oh. Did you tell Park about this?

103
00:09:42,916 --> 00:09:44,542
I didn't.

104
00:09:45,126 --> 00:09:46,169
I said I wouldn't say anything.

105
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:47,796
Good, Kang.
You did great.

106
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:50,799
Look, I can handle the situation now.
You should leave.

107
00:09:50,882 --> 00:09:52,967
I'm going to hand over
the gold bars to Chairman Ahn

108
00:09:53,051 --> 00:09:54,969
-so just go.
-No. No, no, no, Jinman.

109
00:09:55,053 --> 00:09:57,138
Look, we've both been in
this game for years,

110
00:09:57,222 --> 00:09:58,890
and I know you pretty well, yeah?

111
00:09:58,973 --> 00:10:01,017
Now that things turned out
this way,

112
00:10:01,101 --> 00:10:02,852
let's find the casket
and then split the gold.

113
00:10:02,936 --> 00:10:04,646
Nobody's gonna know the two of us took it.

114
00:10:05,396 --> 00:10:07,357
-All I gotta do is kill this woman--
-Hey, asshole.

115
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:09,692
Are you crazy?
What are you doing?

116
00:10:09,776 --> 00:10:11,653
Chairman Ahn is on his way over now,
you idiot,

117
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:13,113
and the gold bars aren't even here.

118
00:10:13,196 --> 00:10:14,948
Where did you bury the casket?

119
00:10:15,031 --> 00:10:17,909
Hey. You--you really need to listen.

120
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:20,954
Just--just, you need
to get outta here. Okay?

121
00:10:22,122 --> 00:10:23,123
Get off her!

122
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:26,709
Hey! Drop the gun!

123
00:10:26,835 --> 00:10:28,795
Drop the gun, you bastard!

124
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:30,630
Just drop it, asshole!

125
00:10:32,090 --> 00:10:33,466
Hey, stop moving around!

126
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:48,815
Fucker!

127
00:10:48,898 --> 00:10:50,233
Fuck you!

128
00:10:53,444 --> 00:10:54,529
Motherfucker!

129
00:11:00,952 --> 00:11:03,955
You fucking bastard!
I did all this...

130
00:11:13,798 --> 00:11:14,799
Woogy.

131
00:11:15,592 --> 00:11:17,510
Shit. Oh, fuck.

132
00:11:21,556 --> 00:11:23,141
Donghoon.

133
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:49,125
Drop it.

134
00:11:50,627 --> 00:11:52,253
You piece of shit!

135
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:57,133
You fucking bastard!

136
00:11:57,217 --> 00:12:00,428
I'm gonna kill you,
you motherfucker!

137
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:01,512
Let him go!

138
00:12:01,596 --> 00:12:03,139
He--he doesn't know anything!

139
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:05,600
He doesn't even know where
the gold bars are!

140
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:07,352
He was just doing what I told him to do!

141
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:10,772
Where are the gold bars?

142
00:12:10,855 --> 00:12:13,149
Tell me or I'll kill this bastard!

143
00:12:14,275 --> 00:12:17,362
You have three seconds!
Three! Two--

144
00:12:17,445 --> 00:12:18,738
Don't do it!
He'll kill me anyway!

145
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:20,490
Stop! No!
I'll tell you after you let him go!

146
00:12:38,841 --> 00:12:40,510
INCOMING CALL
CHAIRMAN AHN GYUSEOK

147
00:13:10,248 --> 00:13:11,291
It's not here, sir.

148
00:13:20,883 --> 00:13:23,011
INCOMING CALL
CHAIRMAN AHN GYUSEOK

149
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:36,357
Ah, this fucking asshole.

150
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,585
Hello?

151
00:13:55,668 --> 00:13:57,128
Did you check it?

152
00:13:57,837 --> 00:13:58,838
Yeah.

153
00:14:00,048 --> 00:14:01,049
What about the rest?

154
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:02,842
Pay first.

155
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:08,014
Give me the number.
I'll send it right away.

156
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:09,849
Okay.

157
00:14:22,153 --> 00:14:25,323
S SINA30@GMOIL.COM

158
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:32,288
COMPOSE EMAIL

159
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:39,670
It's not a big deal.

160
00:14:40,046 --> 00:14:42,840
Just give me whatever drugs you have.

161
00:14:42,924 --> 00:14:44,217
-We don't have that kind of stuff!
-Huh?

162
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:45,676
-We don't--
-You don't have drugs?

163
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:47,053
Right.

164
00:14:47,136 --> 00:14:48,137
Stand still.

165
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:50,181
Idiot.

166
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:51,849
Ah, fuck you.

167
00:14:58,981 --> 00:15:00,775
Please let it slide this time!

168
00:15:01,234 --> 00:15:03,444
If I get arrested again, I really...

169
00:15:08,533 --> 00:15:09,867
Oh, shit.

170
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,710
INCOMING CALL
INTERNATIONAL CALL

171
00:15:36,811 --> 00:15:39,021
Answer the phone.
It's me, Dokyung.

172
00:15:39,105 --> 00:15:41,732
INCOMING CALL

173
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:49,574
I e-mailed you the account link
and password.

174
00:15:49,657 --> 00:15:52,785
I'll wire the money to the account as soon
as the gold bars are taken care of.

175
00:16:00,126 --> 00:16:01,169
Ah, shit.

176
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:04,839
2 MESSAGES SELECTED
DELETE ALL

177
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:28,321
CHAIRMAN AHN GYUSEOK

178
00:16:34,911 --> 00:16:36,204
Where are we going now?

179
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:39,582
Somewhere safe.

180
00:16:51,719 --> 00:16:52,762
Hello, sir.

181
00:16:54,013 --> 00:16:56,849
Hey. Take this. Here.

182
00:16:56,933 --> 00:16:59,310
I caught this one over
at the dead drop earlier.

183
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:02,980
Take it to, uh--what's it called?

184
00:17:03,064 --> 00:17:05,024
Narcotics for analysis.

185
00:17:05,107 --> 00:17:07,610
Oh, and also,
I'll tell the chief about it.

186
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:09,070
Okay, understood.

187
00:17:17,578 --> 00:17:18,579
Sit over there.

188
00:17:41,602 --> 00:17:43,354
Now I might die because of you.

189
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:45,815
Let's talk now.

190
00:17:46,774 --> 00:17:48,359
It's not too late.

191
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:51,612
Look, I know how you feel, okay?

192
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:55,658
Of course you want it.
It's so tempting, right?

193
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:59,370
You don't have any idea what Chairman Ahn
is like, though.

194
00:18:00,871 --> 00:18:05,001
If you don't return the gold bars,
you and I are both going to die.

195
00:18:06,127 --> 00:18:07,587
What's more important to you?

196
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:09,797
The gold bars or your life?

197
00:18:11,132 --> 00:18:13,301
I can't give the chairman back his gold.

198
00:18:14,677 --> 00:18:17,096
Because Lee Dokyung already took half.

199
00:18:17,888 --> 00:18:19,515
So I only have half left.

200
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:23,561
Fuck.

201
00:18:43,623 --> 00:18:47,960
If that's the case,
we'll return half for now, yeah?

202
00:18:48,753 --> 00:18:50,755
And we'll catch Lee Dokyung after.

203
00:18:51,714 --> 00:18:53,674
Do you think Chairman Ahn
will believe that?

204
00:18:54,508 --> 00:18:57,803
Don't you think he would suspect that
you kept the other half for yourself?

205
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:00,973
If that happens...

206
00:19:01,474 --> 00:19:04,477
...you'll have no choice but
to tell him my name eventually.

207
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:06,228
I said I wouldn't tell him.

208
00:19:06,312 --> 00:19:07,313
Okay?

209
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:12,234
You already saw when I was on
the phone earlier talking to Chairman Ahn.

210
00:19:12,318 --> 00:19:13,819
I won't tell him about you.

211
00:19:15,196 --> 00:19:16,405
Where are they?

212
00:19:18,324 --> 00:19:19,742
Why are you trying so hard

213
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:21,994
to give Chairman Ahn back his gold,
anyway?

214
00:19:23,412 --> 00:19:24,747
Isn't it obvious?

215
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:26,666
Huh?

216
00:19:26,749 --> 00:19:29,001
Chairman Ahn is the owner
of that gold.

217
00:19:29,377 --> 00:19:31,253
Once you make me talk...

218
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:34,548
...you'll just try and keep all
the gold for yourself.

219
00:19:35,758 --> 00:19:37,510
That's what all the others tried to do.

220
00:19:38,761 --> 00:19:39,970
Park did that.

221
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:41,597
Cha Yujin, too.

222
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:45,976
Have you considered that maybe I'm not
as greedy as they are?

223
00:19:53,359 --> 00:19:55,152
It's not about greed.

224
00:19:55,236 --> 00:19:57,029
You just don't have the courage for it.

225
00:19:58,072 --> 00:20:00,449
The courage to fight Chairman Ahn and win.

226
00:20:01,575 --> 00:20:03,244
You're just too scared of him.

227
00:20:05,287 --> 00:20:07,039
How much did he promise to give you?

228
00:20:09,083 --> 00:20:10,835
That's none of your business.

229
00:20:11,335 --> 00:20:12,461
I'll double the amount.

230
00:20:14,755 --> 00:20:15,881
Detective.

231
00:20:17,258 --> 00:20:19,510
I'm the one who has
the gold bars right now.

232
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:23,139
Which means I'm the real owner
of the gold, not Chairman Ahn.

233
00:20:23,639 --> 00:20:26,726
So if you wanna get your payment,
it isn't Ahn you need.

234
00:20:26,809 --> 00:20:28,561
I'm the one you should make a deal with.

235
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:33,566
You're a real nut.
You know that?

236
00:20:34,275 --> 00:20:35,276
Huh?

237
00:20:36,277 --> 00:20:38,821
It's like you've totally lost your mind.

238
00:20:39,321 --> 00:20:40,865
You'd better snap out of it, kid.

239
00:20:41,991 --> 00:20:43,868
The gold bars aren't the issue right now.

240
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:48,038
It's that the two of us are gonna die.

241
00:20:48,122 --> 00:20:50,624
If I die,
it's because of you.

242
00:20:50,708 --> 00:20:51,709
Because of you!

243
00:20:52,501 --> 00:20:54,712
And my life is more important to me.

244
00:20:56,297 --> 00:20:58,299
What good is the gold
if you're dead?

245
00:21:00,217 --> 00:21:04,013
I would rather die than live that way.

246
00:21:06,682 --> 00:21:08,100
What?

247
00:21:09,435 --> 00:21:10,478
What'd you say?

248
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:13,814
I would rather be dead...

249
00:21:14,815 --> 00:21:16,567
...than live like you people.

250
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:24,241
HEEJU

251
00:21:36,086 --> 00:21:37,087
Hello?

252
00:21:38,047 --> 00:21:39,507
Hey, did you take care of it?

253
00:21:42,468 --> 00:21:43,469
Yeah.

254
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:48,224
Uh, how's Heeju?

255
00:21:48,933 --> 00:21:50,267
That's none of your business.

256
00:21:51,352 --> 00:21:54,355
From now on, don't even think about
setting foot in Jeongsan ever again.

257
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:56,357
And as for Kim Heeju...

258
00:21:57,441 --> 00:21:59,276
...I need you to stay away from her.

259
00:21:59,985 --> 00:22:02,279
If I ever catch you
hanging around Jeongsan again...

260
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:04,156
...then I swear...

261
00:22:04,740 --> 00:22:06,033
...I will kill you.

262
00:22:07,159 --> 00:22:08,160
Got it?

263
00:22:08,244 --> 00:22:10,454
I--if anything happens to Heeju...

264
00:22:11,956 --> 00:22:12,957
...I'll kill you, too.

265
00:22:14,166 --> 00:22:15,626
I--I'll tell them everything.

266
00:22:16,502 --> 00:22:18,754
Chairman Ahn, Park Hocheol,
the police.

267
00:22:18,838 --> 00:22:20,172
I'll even tell the police everything.

268
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:22,174
As you wish.

269
00:22:22,258 --> 00:22:25,177
Wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait! Wait. Detective, wait.

270
00:22:26,262 --> 00:22:28,806
If I--if I give you the gold bars...

271
00:22:29,598 --> 00:22:30,683
...will you free Heeju?

272
00:22:31,225 --> 00:22:33,435
Did you find where they're hidden?
You know where they are?

273
00:22:38,315 --> 00:22:40,985
Uh, first things first.

274
00:22:41,068 --> 00:22:42,319
Could I speak to Heeju?

275
00:22:42,403 --> 00:22:43,404
Are you serious?

276
00:22:48,367 --> 00:22:49,618
Shit.

277
00:22:55,291 --> 00:22:56,333
Sir.

278
00:22:56,417 --> 00:22:58,043
-Hmm?
-Someone's looking for you.

279
00:22:58,127 --> 00:22:59,128
Hmm?

280
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:05,009
Hello.

281
00:23:05,092 --> 00:23:06,635
Detective Kim.

282
00:23:12,308 --> 00:23:13,559
So what happened?

283
00:23:15,477 --> 00:23:17,730
I was up all night long waiting for you.

284
00:23:19,023 --> 00:23:23,652
Well, I caught Ju Haran and we
were heading to where the mine is located.

285
00:23:23,736 --> 00:23:26,071
Then some car just suddenly hit us
from behind and we--

286
00:23:26,155 --> 00:23:27,197
Enough.

287
00:23:27,907 --> 00:23:29,116
Get to the point.

288
00:23:30,284 --> 00:23:31,619
So you lost her.

289
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:33,746
And the casket, too.

290
00:23:34,330 --> 00:23:35,873
Yeah.

291
00:23:35,956 --> 00:23:37,666
You don't know whose car it was?

292
00:23:38,292 --> 00:23:40,419
I think the car was Park Hocheol's.

293
00:23:41,670 --> 00:23:43,756
Seems like Yes Money
is working with him now.

294
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:47,301
Gitae, too?

295
00:23:51,221 --> 00:23:52,932
I don't know how much
of this I should believe

296
00:23:53,015 --> 00:23:54,141
and how much I shouldn't.

297
00:23:54,224 --> 00:23:56,101
Just give me a few--no.

298
00:23:56,852 --> 00:23:58,062
Just give me one more day.

299
00:23:58,145 --> 00:23:59,855
I'm tracking the car through
surveillance footage.

300
00:23:59,939 --> 00:24:00,940
I know I'll find it soon.

301
00:24:02,942 --> 00:24:04,568
Look, Kim Jinman.

302
00:24:05,069 --> 00:24:08,113
Do you know why I never
told Hocheol about the gold bars?

303
00:24:09,323 --> 00:24:10,574
The truth is,

304
00:24:10,658 --> 00:24:13,327
I was never able
to get any collateral on that man.

305
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:16,622
The people with something to protect...

306
00:24:17,414 --> 00:24:19,667
...they wouldn't even dream
of betraying me.

307
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:23,045
Whether it's their child,
their life, money, or beliefs.

308
00:24:23,128 --> 00:24:25,130
Most people don't want
to lose those things.

309
00:24:25,214 --> 00:24:26,423
They're worth too much.

310
00:24:26,507 --> 00:24:28,801
But Park,
he doesn't have anything like that.

311
00:24:28,884 --> 00:24:32,513
But I don't have anything
that's worth protecting.

312
00:24:32,596 --> 00:24:35,683
Your ex-wife.
What was her name, again?

313
00:24:36,016 --> 00:24:37,017
Yeo Sunok.

314
00:24:38,018 --> 00:24:39,228
She's in the hospital.

315
00:24:41,271 --> 00:24:42,856
You abandoned your wife.

316
00:24:43,232 --> 00:24:45,317
Yet you're still doing whatever it takes.

317
00:24:45,401 --> 00:24:48,153
I guess you're trying
to hold onto what you have left.

318
00:24:48,862 --> 00:24:51,865
And you're just really desperate
to stay alive.

319
00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:56,662
Sure, why not wait one more day?

320
00:24:57,788 --> 00:24:59,915
I promise I'll find the gold bars.

321
00:25:01,125 --> 00:25:02,793
I'll do whatever it takes, sir.

322
00:25:04,044 --> 00:25:06,588
Just give me one gold bar
like you said you would.

323
00:25:07,548 --> 00:25:10,634
That way I can finally start living
a decent life.

324
00:25:14,304 --> 00:25:15,305
Okay.

325
00:25:48,714 --> 00:25:49,840
Hey, Sunok.

326
00:25:51,508 --> 00:25:54,011
No matter how many times I try
to save your daughter...

327
00:25:54,803 --> 00:25:56,597
...she just won't listen.

328
00:25:58,432 --> 00:26:00,976
Who do you think she got that from,
I wonder?

329
00:26:18,452 --> 00:26:19,453
Hey.

330
00:26:22,498 --> 00:26:23,582
Yeah.

331
00:26:25,834 --> 00:26:27,753
Uh, what?

332
00:26:30,297 --> 00:26:32,549
Uh, this? Huh?

333
00:26:33,258 --> 00:26:34,301
Okay.

334
00:26:37,387 --> 00:26:39,098
-Heeju.
-Huh?

335
00:26:39,723 --> 00:26:41,141
Where's Heeju?

336
00:26:41,683 --> 00:26:45,479
Oh, yeah. She--she's okay.
I've got her. She's fine.

337
00:26:49,316 --> 00:26:50,526
She's...

338
00:26:52,069 --> 00:26:55,280
...she's not like us, is she?

339
00:26:56,031 --> 00:26:57,950
Oh, yeah, yeah.
She's not.

340
00:27:01,745 --> 00:27:02,746
Let...

341
00:27:05,791 --> 00:27:09,128
...let her live the way she wants to.

342
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:15,926
Let her go her own way.

343
00:27:16,009 --> 00:27:17,469
Mm-hmm.

344
00:27:19,721 --> 00:27:24,560
You and I already lived our lives.

345
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,523
Mm-hmm.

346
00:27:39,408 --> 00:27:40,659
Jinman.

347
00:27:44,705 --> 00:27:47,457
Thank you, Jinman.

348
00:27:52,546 --> 00:27:54,256
Thank you.

349
00:27:59,011 --> 00:28:01,471
I'm gonna rest now.

350
00:29:14,336 --> 00:29:15,921
I'm so sorry.

351
00:29:20,384 --> 00:29:21,635
Ah, shit.

352
00:29:51,331 --> 00:29:52,457
No.

353
00:29:53,083 --> 00:29:54,084
Sunok.

354
00:29:55,335 --> 00:29:56,545
Sunok!

355
00:29:58,922 --> 00:30:00,090
Sunok.

356
00:30:02,092 --> 00:30:03,427
Sunok.

357
00:30:04,553 --> 00:30:05,887
Sunok.

358
00:30:15,272 --> 00:30:22,279
YES MONEY

359
00:30:40,380 --> 00:30:41,631
Whoa.

360
00:30:43,550 --> 00:30:45,302
What brings you all the way here?

361
00:30:47,220 --> 00:30:48,680
Have a seat.

362
00:30:51,516 --> 00:30:52,851
Go ahead.
Sit down.

363
00:30:53,977 --> 00:30:55,437
You want a tea or something?

364
00:31:05,113 --> 00:31:06,114
Hey.

365
00:31:07,407 --> 00:31:10,243
I told your guys that I wanted them out
of the hospital.

366
00:31:11,745 --> 00:31:12,996
They didn't tell you?

367
00:31:16,249 --> 00:31:18,168
Why do you keep doing this?

368
00:31:18,251 --> 00:31:20,003
They can't even go to the hospital?

369
00:31:20,087 --> 00:31:22,255
They were all there
to see the doctor.

370
00:31:22,339 --> 00:31:24,549
I didn't come here
to joke around, asshole.

371
00:31:34,726 --> 00:31:36,103
Whose side are you on?

372
00:31:36,728 --> 00:31:39,439
Chairman Ahn or Park Hocheol?

373
00:31:40,607 --> 00:31:42,192
What's that supposed to mean?

374
00:31:44,027 --> 00:31:45,529
Hey, this is Yes Money!

375
00:31:45,612 --> 00:31:48,448
And the Chairman owns Yes Money
so obviously I'm on his side.

376
00:31:48,990 --> 00:31:50,117
Are you sure?

377
00:31:51,201 --> 00:31:52,744
Yeah, of course I am.

378
00:31:54,037 --> 00:31:57,415
So Chairman Ahn sent those guys
to the hospital then, right?

379
00:31:58,834 --> 00:32:00,377
Give the Chairman this message.

380
00:32:01,711 --> 00:32:03,088
You can pull all your guys out.

381
00:32:07,425 --> 00:32:09,511
Because Yeo Sunok is dead now.

382
00:32:27,404 --> 00:32:28,989
Yes.
We'll take you in this car.

383
00:32:35,537 --> 00:32:37,414
-Thank you.
-Oh. Thank you very much.

384
00:32:56,933 --> 00:32:58,310
-Good shot!
-Good shot.

385
00:33:07,068 --> 00:33:09,237
-Oh, nice shot.
-Wow, nice shot.

386
00:33:14,826 --> 00:33:17,537
Excuse me! Hello.
Excuse me.

387
00:33:20,582 --> 00:33:22,167
Hello there. Hi.

388
00:33:23,376 --> 00:33:26,254
Sorry, give me one second.

389
00:33:26,338 --> 00:33:27,672
Hang on here.

390
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:33,595
Yes, excuse me. I wanted to ask,
are you guys from Cambodia, by any chance?

391
00:33:35,138 --> 00:33:38,558
Here. Look.
You can read this.

392
00:33:38,642 --> 00:33:39,643
Who are you?

393
00:33:40,644 --> 00:33:42,270
Shit, you guys know how
to speak Korean?

394
00:33:43,146 --> 00:33:44,940
So you must have seen this,
right?

395
00:33:45,732 --> 00:33:48,193
He's the governor, you know, huh?

396
00:33:48,276 --> 00:33:49,444
This guy. It's him.

397
00:33:49,527 --> 00:33:50,737
-Mr. Ahn.
-Oh.

398
00:33:50,820 --> 00:33:51,821
So glad you could make it.

399
00:33:52,155 --> 00:33:53,490
-Nice to meet you. Hello.
-How do you do?

400
00:33:53,573 --> 00:33:55,158
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

401
00:33:55,242 --> 00:33:56,701
All these people here...

402
00:33:57,244 --> 00:33:58,787
...all of them are fake.

403
00:33:59,287 --> 00:34:00,413
Okay?

404
00:34:01,248 --> 00:34:03,250
So you came here in the middle
of the game?

405
00:34:03,333 --> 00:34:05,418
Who told you that absolute nonsense?

406
00:34:06,586 --> 00:34:08,922
All I've heard is that he's one
of the Geumseong guys.

407
00:34:09,005 --> 00:34:10,924
Could you describe what he looked like?

408
00:34:11,549 --> 00:34:14,052
Did he have a scar anywhere on his face?

409
00:34:17,764 --> 00:34:19,307
Park Hocheol.

410
00:34:20,684 --> 00:34:22,185
That idiot.

411
00:34:22,269 --> 00:34:24,312
I knew he'd try something eventually.

412
00:34:26,189 --> 00:34:27,649
How about this?
The governor.

413
00:34:27,732 --> 00:34:30,318
If you're suspicious,
do you wanna go see him?

414
00:34:30,402 --> 00:34:31,861
In person, I mean.

415
00:34:31,945 --> 00:34:34,322
We don't fully trust that man,
either.

416
00:34:36,866 --> 00:34:37,909
We just...

417
00:34:39,035 --> 00:34:41,830
...we want to know if the gold bars
are kept safe.

418
00:34:41,913 --> 00:34:44,666
Well, did you report it yet?

419
00:34:47,127 --> 00:34:48,128
Not yet, no.

420
00:34:50,547 --> 00:34:52,132
Okay, then.

421
00:34:57,012 --> 00:34:58,847
CALLING
YES MONEY KO GITAE

422
00:35:03,476 --> 00:35:04,686
Hey, President Ko.

423
00:35:05,562 --> 00:35:07,856
Our Cambodian guests have asked me
if it's possible

424
00:35:07,939 --> 00:35:09,441
to show them the casket today.

425
00:35:10,108 --> 00:35:11,484
Could you take care of it?

426
00:35:29,794 --> 00:35:31,046
Afternoon, sir.

427
00:35:31,588 --> 00:35:32,631
We're all ready to go.

428
00:35:50,148 --> 00:35:52,150
Where are we going?

429
00:35:52,651 --> 00:35:54,486
You wanted to see the casket, right?

430
00:35:55,779 --> 00:35:56,780
We're almost there.

431
00:36:17,300 --> 00:36:18,468
President Ko.

432
00:36:19,719 --> 00:36:21,096
You sure it's here?

433
00:36:21,638 --> 00:36:23,807
I think so. I haven't been out here
in a while, though.

434
00:36:24,724 --> 00:36:26,226
Is it this way?

435
00:36:27,352 --> 00:36:29,145
Hey, this the right place?

436
00:36:31,439 --> 00:36:33,316
-Then why..
-This is Socom.

437
00:36:34,567 --> 00:36:36,736
No, we're still in Jeongsan.

438
00:36:40,115 --> 00:36:42,075
You scared me!
Shit. Fucking hell.

439
00:36:46,705 --> 00:36:48,248
Whoa. Hey, hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

440
00:37:22,532 --> 00:37:24,409
President Ko.

441
00:37:25,285 --> 00:37:28,830
Tell Chairman Ahn to bring
the casket right away.

442
00:37:28,913 --> 00:37:29,914
Yes, sir.

443
00:37:33,626 --> 00:37:35,503
Oh, shit. We're really fucked.

444
00:37:37,213 --> 00:37:38,757
We're so fucked.

445
00:37:49,684 --> 00:37:52,020
DIRECTOR PARK HOCHEOL

446
00:37:56,941 --> 00:37:59,819
-Hello, sir.
-Did you find that prick Woogy?

447
00:38:00,945 --> 00:38:02,363
Well, he got away from us.

448
00:38:03,072 --> 00:38:04,491
Finding him isn't easy.

449
00:38:07,035 --> 00:38:09,078
What about the jewelry store? What?

450
00:38:09,746 --> 00:38:10,830
Nothing from them yet?

451
00:38:11,372 --> 00:38:13,249
No, not yet.

452
00:38:13,333 --> 00:38:16,961
He was last seen over at Lucky Jewelry.
He was selling the gold there.

453
00:38:18,129 --> 00:38:19,547
It's him for sure.

454
00:38:19,631 --> 00:38:22,801
Choi, the owner,
he sent me the surveillance footage.

455
00:38:23,927 --> 00:38:26,846
That prick will show up again.
He's still got gold to sell.

456
00:38:27,764 --> 00:38:30,350
Tell him to stay alert.
Watch carefully.

457
00:38:31,351 --> 00:38:33,478
Yeah, will do.

458
00:38:34,395 --> 00:38:36,231
My boys are keeping an eye on the place.

459
00:38:38,024 --> 00:38:42,654
If I hear anything from Lucky Jewelry,
or anywhere else,

460
00:38:42,737 --> 00:38:44,072
I'll let you know right away, sir.

461
00:38:44,155 --> 00:38:48,493
LUCKY JEWELRY

462
00:38:55,250 --> 00:38:57,043
LUCKY JEWELRY, DAEJEONG

463
00:38:57,126 --> 00:39:01,923
LUCKY JEWELRY

464
00:39:26,364 --> 00:39:27,365
Heeju.

465
00:39:30,118 --> 00:39:31,995
Is this Lee Dokyung?

466
00:39:34,122 --> 00:39:36,583
Bet it is. Yeah.

467
00:39:36,666 --> 00:39:38,376
Lee Dokyung, am I right?

468
00:39:39,669 --> 00:39:41,337
This is the police calling.

469
00:39:41,421 --> 00:39:43,882
I'm detective Kim Jinman
with Investigations.

470
00:39:46,259 --> 00:39:48,970
I heard you're in possession
of half of the gold bars.

471
00:39:53,850 --> 00:39:54,851
Are you listening?

472
00:39:56,060 --> 00:39:57,103
Good.

473
00:39:57,979 --> 00:39:59,731
Right now we're holding Kim Heeju.

474
00:40:01,649 --> 00:40:03,318
But, I think we can release her.

475
00:40:04,068 --> 00:40:05,528
We should make a deal.

476
00:40:06,529 --> 00:40:07,655
Where should I go?

477
00:40:12,243 --> 00:40:15,622
Uh, you know that street in Daejeong
with all the jewelry stores?

478
00:40:16,789 --> 00:40:18,833
There's a shop called
Lucky Jewelry there.

479
00:40:18,917 --> 00:40:22,170
You can sell your gold bars.
They take them at that store, 'kay?

480
00:40:24,047 --> 00:40:28,217
Once you're finished with all that,
make sure you give me a call immediately.

481
00:40:28,301 --> 00:40:30,470
I'll give you
a meeting location afterwards.

482
00:40:31,930 --> 00:40:33,056
See you tomorrow.

483
00:40:34,474 --> 00:40:41,481
JG JANGGAK TRADE INC

484
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:02,001
How is it in here?

485
00:41:05,755 --> 00:41:07,173
I'm gonna release you now.

486
00:41:07,840 --> 00:41:09,842
Leave by the end of the day.
Take the gold, too.

487
00:41:12,345 --> 00:41:14,013
Actually, you know what?

488
00:41:14,097 --> 00:41:15,348
Forget about the gold.

489
00:41:16,140 --> 00:41:17,433
You just need to get out of here.

490
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:20,478
Don't go to the hospital.

491
00:41:22,689 --> 00:41:24,315
Don't go to the pawnshop, either.

492
00:41:25,775 --> 00:41:30,029
Chairman Ahn's out there,
looking all over Jeongsan to find you.

493
00:41:30,113 --> 00:41:31,406
He has guys everywhere.

494
00:41:34,158 --> 00:41:35,326
Why did you...

495
00:41:37,829 --> 00:41:39,038
What happened?

496
00:41:40,331 --> 00:41:42,333
You just suddenly changed your mind?

497
00:41:44,377 --> 00:41:45,795
I've been, uh...

498
00:41:46,963 --> 00:41:48,548
...I've been thinking about it.

499
00:41:51,718 --> 00:41:54,012
And you might've had
the right idea all along.

500
00:41:56,097 --> 00:41:59,851
Instead of returning all the gold bars
to Chairman Ahn just for peanuts...

501
00:42:00,810 --> 00:42:01,811
...I was thinking...

502
00:42:02,645 --> 00:42:05,481
...I should just work out a
good deal with you directly.

503
00:42:06,232 --> 00:42:07,859
You said it yourself.

504
00:42:07,942 --> 00:42:11,154
Right now you're the one
with the gold bars, right?

505
00:42:11,946 --> 00:42:12,989
That's what you said.

506
00:42:15,324 --> 00:42:16,743
How much will you give me?

507
00:42:18,119 --> 00:42:19,412
How much do you want?

508
00:42:21,247 --> 00:42:24,625
Well, you said you'd double what
the Chairman offered.

509
00:42:25,585 --> 00:42:26,711
I want 20, then.

510
00:42:27,295 --> 00:42:28,504
He originally offered to give me 10.

511
00:42:30,465 --> 00:42:31,716
Let's go.

512
00:42:31,799 --> 00:42:33,384
No.

513
00:42:33,468 --> 00:42:35,470
Forget it.
I'll stay right here in this cell.

514
00:42:36,471 --> 00:42:38,181
You can just send me to prison.

515
00:42:41,225 --> 00:42:42,226
Fine.

516
00:42:43,561 --> 00:42:45,521
Be like that, then, huh?

517
00:42:46,355 --> 00:42:48,566
And never trust anybody
in this world who isn't you.

518
00:42:50,401 --> 00:42:51,944
What a great way to live.

519
00:42:54,155 --> 00:42:56,407
Give me two, then.
Just two.

520
00:42:57,742 --> 00:42:59,827
I can live with two gold bars.

521
00:42:59,911 --> 00:43:02,455
He only offered me one.
So give me two.

522
00:43:03,122 --> 00:43:04,123
We have a deal?

523
00:43:04,582 --> 00:43:05,958
Here.

524
00:43:13,257 --> 00:43:14,717
Hey, why don't you try pulling
your hands out?

525
00:43:14,801 --> 00:43:16,511
They look small enough
to slip out.

526
00:43:17,261 --> 00:43:18,679
No. No, they won't.

527
00:43:20,181 --> 00:43:21,224
Come on.

528
00:43:23,184 --> 00:43:25,353
I guess they're not that small.

529
00:43:34,570 --> 00:43:35,696
Here.

530
00:43:36,864 --> 00:43:37,865
These are your things.

531
00:43:41,494 --> 00:43:45,123
I already spoke to Woogy
and Lee Dokyung over the phone.

532
00:43:46,791 --> 00:43:48,918
I told them you're being held
at the police station.

533
00:43:49,836 --> 00:43:51,546
You won't get any calls
from those two.

534
00:43:51,921 --> 00:43:55,716
And even if they try to reach you,
don't ever pick up the phone.

535
00:43:56,425 --> 00:43:57,468
You can be tracked.

536
00:43:58,386 --> 00:43:59,387
Got it?

537
00:43:59,971 --> 00:44:04,684
JEONGSAN POLICE ALWAYS
SERVES YOU WITH CARE

538
00:44:12,066 --> 00:44:13,609
In my glove box,
there's a gun.

539
00:44:15,153 --> 00:44:16,612
It's there if you need it.

540
00:44:18,030 --> 00:44:21,450
But you better not use it unless
it's absolutely necessary.

541
00:44:21,993 --> 00:44:23,035
Understand?

542
00:44:24,370 --> 00:44:25,371
Okay.

543
00:44:25,913 --> 00:44:27,665
Thank you very much.

544
00:44:27,748 --> 00:44:29,125
No need to thank me for this.

545
00:44:29,208 --> 00:44:31,460
Just give me my gold bars
before you leave.

546
00:44:31,544 --> 00:44:33,671
I'm not kidding.
I'll tell everyone.

547
00:44:52,273 --> 00:44:53,274
Hey, sir?

548
00:44:55,693 --> 00:44:57,195
Look after Sunok for me.

549
00:45:44,825 --> 00:45:45,952
YES MONEY KO GITAE

550
00:45:46,035 --> 00:45:47,453
CALLING...
YES MONEY KO GITAE

551
00:45:52,166 --> 00:45:53,292
What's goin' on?

552
00:45:53,542 --> 00:45:54,961
Is Park still in contact with you?

553
00:45:55,711 --> 00:45:57,922
Do you think I have a death wish?
I'm not crazy.

554
00:45:58,839 --> 00:46:00,967
I know you're acting,
so just cut the bullshit.

555
00:46:02,260 --> 00:46:03,678
Give Park this message.

556
00:46:04,845 --> 00:46:06,389
I can help catch Lee Dokyung.

557
00:46:06,472 --> 00:46:08,015
And if he finds the casket...

558
00:46:08,891 --> 00:46:09,976
...I want a billion.

559
00:46:11,394 --> 00:46:12,937
No, no, no.
Two billion.

560
00:46:13,020 --> 00:46:14,730
Two billion sounds good, 'kay?

561
00:46:15,982 --> 00:46:17,191
I won't wait for long.

562
00:46:28,202 --> 00:46:30,162
Hello, Chairman. Yes.

563
00:46:31,163 --> 00:46:32,748
I finally found Lee Dokyung.

564
00:46:33,374 --> 00:46:35,376
And we might as well take care
of Park Hocheol

565
00:46:35,459 --> 00:46:36,794
at the same time, if we can.

566
00:46:37,878 --> 00:46:42,091
I'll have President Ko send his guys
to, uh, Lucky Jewelry tomorrow, okay?

567
00:46:43,092 --> 00:46:44,635
I'll make sure everyone's there.

568
00:47:00,943 --> 00:47:02,320
Three.

569
00:47:09,035 --> 00:47:11,245
When's the earliest boat out
of the country leaving?

570
00:47:11,329 --> 00:47:12,872
I don't care where it's going.

571
00:47:13,873 --> 00:47:17,084
The first boat would be the one
the day after tomorrow.

572
00:47:17,585 --> 00:47:19,920
Why are you asking all of a sudden?
Did something happen?

573
00:47:20,004 --> 00:47:21,047
I need a ticket.

574
00:47:21,130 --> 00:47:24,091
For a car and a passenger,
like the last one.

575
00:47:24,175 --> 00:47:26,594
Yeah, I can do that.
Who's getting on the boat?

576
00:47:28,512 --> 00:47:29,555
I will.

577
00:47:29,638 --> 00:47:30,723
Huh?

578
00:47:31,182 --> 00:47:32,850
What on Earth is going on here?

579
00:47:33,434 --> 00:47:35,978
Are you both gonna travel separately on
the same boat?

580
00:47:37,396 --> 00:47:38,397
What?

581
00:47:38,481 --> 00:47:42,485
Well, your boyfriend came by earlier
and he asked me for a ferry ticket, too.

582
00:47:43,194 --> 00:47:46,489
He wanted a ticket for himself
and one car, just like you.

583
00:47:46,572 --> 00:47:47,990
And he bought his car here.

584
00:48:29,240 --> 00:48:30,282
If I...

585
00:48:30,574 --> 00:48:33,786
...if I give you the gold bars,
will you free Heeju?

586
00:48:37,039 --> 00:48:38,165
Shit.

587
00:48:48,634 --> 00:48:49,677
Fuck.

588
00:49:10,698 --> 00:49:11,699
Hello?

589
00:49:11,782 --> 00:49:14,118
Hello, sir, this is Woogy.

590
00:49:14,201 --> 00:49:16,203
-Hello?
-I'm sorry.

591
00:49:16,287 --> 00:49:18,414
Sir, please, help me.

592
00:49:18,497 --> 00:49:20,082
I'll explain everything.

593
00:49:20,166 --> 00:49:21,333
Where are you?

594
00:49:21,792 --> 00:49:23,878
I--I'm in the barn.

595
00:49:23,961 --> 00:49:25,129
The barn?

596
00:49:25,212 --> 00:49:26,213
Yes.

597
00:49:26,630 --> 00:49:28,257
Okay. Just hold on, then.

598
00:49:28,340 --> 00:49:29,675
I'll be right there.

599
00:49:29,758 --> 00:49:31,051
Okay.

600
00:49:31,552 --> 00:49:33,721
-I appreciate it.
-Sure.

601
00:49:33,804 --> 00:49:35,222
That asshole Woogy's at the barn.

602
00:49:35,306 --> 00:49:36,474
-Let's go. Come on.
-Let's get out of here.

603
00:51:31,088 --> 00:51:32,756
Fuck, it's here.

604
00:52:17,760 --> 00:52:19,011
Captain?

605
00:52:20,971 --> 00:52:22,222
The fuck?

606
00:52:22,306 --> 00:52:24,058
What are you doing here?

607
00:52:24,141 --> 00:52:25,309
I can explain.

608
00:52:25,392 --> 00:52:27,227
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

609
00:52:28,395 --> 00:52:31,690
It's Heeju.
She's been arrested.

610
00:52:36,654 --> 00:52:38,197
I'm Heeju's childhood friend.

611
00:52:38,656 --> 00:52:40,282
And her business partner.

612
00:52:40,366 --> 00:52:42,034
The bars. The bars!
I helped her.

613
00:52:42,117 --> 00:52:44,578
I was the one who sold the bars.
I did that.

614
00:52:44,662 --> 00:52:45,871
Cut the crap and shut up.

615
00:52:46,413 --> 00:52:48,207
Go and grab the gold bars.
Move it!

616
00:52:48,290 --> 00:52:49,625
No, hold on!

617
00:52:49,708 --> 00:52:51,418
We don't have time for this, huh?

618
00:52:51,877 --> 00:52:54,672
We need to use those gold bars
to get Heeju out of the police station.

619
00:52:55,172 --> 00:52:57,675
Detective Kim Jinman.
You know who he is, right?

620
00:52:58,342 --> 00:52:59,885
He works for the Geumseong guys.

621
00:53:00,469 --> 00:53:01,720
Yeah?

622
00:53:01,804 --> 00:53:03,514
If we don't get her out
and if she doesn't confess,

623
00:53:03,597 --> 00:53:05,724
he'll hand her over to Geumseong
and Chairman Ahn and his thugs.

624
00:53:05,808 --> 00:53:06,809
Cut the bullshit.

625
00:53:06,892 --> 00:53:09,895
I'm not gonna listen to some asshole
that's been blinded by all this gold.

626
00:53:10,396 --> 00:53:12,606
Take them out. Now!

627
00:53:13,524 --> 00:53:14,733
Fine.

628
00:53:15,401 --> 00:53:16,819
We really don't have time for this shit.

629
00:53:20,781 --> 00:53:23,158
What the fuck, captain? Huh?

630
00:53:23,242 --> 00:53:24,868
You already have half
the fucking gold bars.

631
00:53:24,952 --> 00:53:26,620
You really had to come back for more?

632
00:53:27,955 --> 00:53:29,373
Shut your mouth.

633
00:53:30,082 --> 00:53:31,542
-Keep looking.
-I am looking.

634
00:53:32,042 --> 00:53:33,794
I don't know where they could be, either,
for fuck's sake.

635
00:53:37,214 --> 00:53:38,507
I'm lookin'!

636
00:53:38,590 --> 00:53:39,717
Just wait a second.

637
00:54:21,508 --> 00:54:22,509
HAENGBOK PAWNSHOP

638
00:54:28,724 --> 00:54:29,933
Dammit.

639
00:54:32,186 --> 00:54:33,395
You motherfucker.

640
00:54:37,816 --> 00:54:39,193
The fuck.
